Subject: wireless-extensions: force WIRELESS_EXT/WEXT_PRIV on, restore ndo_do_ioctl fallback

ASK userspace tools (cmm, fmc, dpa_app) and several legacy ioctls
issued by VyOS userspace use SIOCSIWxxx wireless-extension ioctls as
a generic netdev escape hatch even on non-wireless interfaces. The
upstream defaults leave WIRELESS_EXT and WEXT_PRIV unconditionally off
on builds without a wireless driver, and wireless_process_ioctl()
returns -EOPNOTSUPP without consulting the netdev's ndo_do_ioctl.

This patch:
  - flips WIRELESS_EXT and WEXT_PRIV to def_bool y so the wext core is
    always linked in (we have no wireless drivers, but we keep the ABI),
  - adds a fallback in wireless_process_ioctl() that calls the driver's
    ndo_do_ioctl handler before giving up with -EOPNOTSUPP.

Refreshed for Linux 6.18.x:
  - WEXT_SPY symbol was removed upstream; the historic hunk that flipped
    it to def_bool y is no longer applicable.
  - wext-core.c::wireless_process_ioctl() context shifted (the function
    moved from ~L984 to ~L943 between 6.6 and 6.18); hunk re-anchored.

diff --git a/net/wireless/Kconfig b/net/wireless/Kconfig
--- a/net/wireless/Kconfig
+++ b/net/wireless/Kconfig
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
 config WIRELESS_EXT
-	bool
+	def_bool y
 
 config WEXT_CORE
 	def_bool y
@@ -13,7 +13,7 @@ config WEXT_PROC
 	depends on WEXT_CORE
 
 config WEXT_PRIV
-	bool
+	def_bool y
 
 config CFG80211
 	tristate "cfg80211 - wireless configuration API"
diff --git a/net/wireless/wext-core.c b/net/wireless/wext-core.c
--- a/net/wireless/wext-core.c
+++ b/net/wireless/wext-core.c
@@ -980,6 +980,9 @@ static int wireless_process_ioctl(struct net *net, struct iwreq *iwr,
 		else if (private)
 			return private(dev, iwr, cmd, info, handler);
 	}
+	/* Old driver API : call driver ioctl handler */
+	if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_do_ioctl)
+		return dev->netdev_ops->ndo_do_ioctl(dev, (struct ifreq *)iwr, cmd);
 	return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 }
 
